// gitui theme — theme-reactive. Named ANSI colors only, so gitui inherits whatever
// Ghostty theme the current window uses (default, g0-g9, SSH themes). Overrides ONLY
// the defaults that are low-contrast on dark/pastel themes; everything else keeps
// gitui's default (named/Reset), which already adapts to the terminal palette.
//
// Root cause of the unreadable command bar: gitui's default command/help bar is
// command_fg=White on cmdbar_bg=Blue. In Catppuccin Mocha (and other pastel themes)
// ANSI "Blue" is a LIGHT pastel (#89b4fa), so white text on it washes out. Using
// Reset for the bar background falls back to the terminal's (dark) background, so
// light command text is readable on every theme. Same washout hits the default
// selection (Blue bg) — DarkGray keeps the highlight visible with readable text.
//
// ratatui color names: Gray = ANSI 7 (white), DarkGray = ANSI 8 (bright black),
// White = ANSI 15 (bright white). Format `key: Some("Name")` per gitui THEMES.md;
// keys match `impl Default for Theme` in gitui's src/ui/style.rs (v0.28.1).
(
    cmdbar_bg:    Some("Reset"),
    command_fg:   Some("White"),
    disabled_fg:  Some("Gray"),
    selection_bg: Some("DarkGray"),
    selection_fg: Some("White"),
)
